g.text: UML Diagram: DataType ContactInformation in Context
- Move the mouse cursor over a name to see more information.
- Click on a name to go to the corresponding page.
- The use of the data type is represented here by a dotted line (not formal UML).

a.title: ― Address: Location address identifying each part of the address as separate elements, identifying the type of address, the level of privacy associated with the release of the address, and a flag to identify the preferred address for contact.
a.xlink:title: ― Address: Location address identifying each part of the address as separate elements, identifying the type of address, the level of privacy associated with the release of the address, and a flag to identify the preferred address for contact.

a.title: ― Email: An e-mail address which conforms to the internet format (RFC 822) including its type and time period for which it is valid.
a.xlink:title: ― Email: An e-mail address which conforms to the internet format (RFC 822) including its type and time period for which it is valid.

a.title: ― ElectronicMessageSystem: Any non-email means of relaying a message electronically. This would include text messaging, Skype, Twitter, ICQ, or other emerging means of electronic message conveyance.
a.xlink:title: ― ElectronicMessageSystem: Any non-email means of relaying a message electronically. This would include text messaging, Skype, Twitter, ICQ, or other emerging means of electronic message conveyance.

a.title: ― Telephone: Details of a telephone number including the number, type of telephone number, a privacy setting and an indication of whether this is the preferred contact number.
a.xlink:title: ― Telephone: Details of a telephone number including the number, type of telephone number, a privacy setting and an indication of whether this is the preferred contact number.

a.title: ― WebLink: A web site (normally a URL) with information on type of site, privacy flag, and effective dates.
a.xlink:title: ― WebLink: A web site (normally a URL) with information on type of site, privacy flag, and effective dates.

a.title: ― LicenseInformation: Information about any relevant license.
a.xlink:title: ― LicenseInformation: Information about any relevant license.

a.title: ― AgentInRole: A reference to an agent (organization, individual, or machine) including a role for that agent in the context of this specific reference.
a.xlink:title: ― AgentInRole: A reference to an agent (organization, individual, or machine) including a role for that agent in the context of this specific reference.

a.title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.
a.xlink:title: ― Reference: Provides a way of pointing to resources outside of the information described in the set of DDI-CDI metadata.

a.title: ― Individual: A person. (See for example the W3C Friend of a Friend Ontology - http://xmlns.com/foaf/spec/#term_Person).

a.title: ― Organization: Collection of people organized within a framework of authority that can perform an act or be associated with another agent.

a.title: ― OrganizationName: Names by which the organization is known. Use the attribute isFormal with a value of True to designate the legal or formal name of the organization. Names may be typed with typeOfOrganizationName to indicate their appropriate usage.
